text: Two ships of the Royal Navy have borne the name HMS Dexterous or HMS Dextrous: * was a gun-brig of 12 guns launched at Eling in 1805 that the Navy sold in 1816. * HMS Dextrous was a screw frigate ordered in 1861, with the order being canceled in 1863. Category:Royal Navy ship names
title: HMS Dexterous
